		<!-- message -->
		<div>The reason people like to debate politics at places like The Glade is you end up with a good mix of people who share a common interest but have many diverse opinions.  Strictly political sites have one slant or another.  Consequently, you don't get much debate just echoing and flaming.  At places like Glade you get intelligent, divers, and yes often passionate debate.  Sometimes tempers flair and people may say mean things, but really if you give more than two seconds of though to something somebody who doesn't really know you says about you on a message board you have real self esteem issues.<br />
 <br />
Instead of banning politics create a separate enter at your own risk section.  Or you could require all political threads to be labeled like: <u>[Politics] Why you are wrong and Nater will be our next president.</u> Then people who are not interested can just stay away.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
